<li> It's okay to feel overwhelmed and allow yourself time to grieve.</li>
<li> Take all the time you need to heal; your grief is valid.</li>
<li> Know that your feelings are normal and that healing takes time.</li>
<li> Remember the good times and celebrate (deceased's name)'s life.</li>
<li> Allow yourself to feel your emotions without judgment.</li>
<li> Find comfort in the love and support of those around you.</li>
<li> Embrace the memories you have and cherish them always.</li>
<li> Your loved one's memory will live on in your heart forever.</li>
